text: The A5 is an autoroute (motorway) in France. It was built in 1990 to lower the amount of cars on the A6. It goes from Paris to the Langres area. It is a toll road. The autoroute is about long. It is part of the E54, E511, and E17 European routes. ==Exits and junctions== Exit/Junction Destination La Francilienne/ Savigny-le-Temple Savigny-Plessis, Lieusaint, Moissy-Cramayel Lieusaint, Moissy-Cramayel Eastbound only Savigny-centre Eastbound only Savigny - Parc d'Activites Westbound only Cesson-Vert St Denis Marne la Valee, Melun Saint-Germain- Laxis Châtillon-la-Borde Forges Marolles-sur-Seine Border between Seine-et-Marne (Ile-de-France) and Yonne (Burgundy) Sens, Provins, Orléans Villeneuve-l'Archevêque, Nogent sur Seine, St. Florentin Border between Yonne (Burgundy) and Aube (Champagne-Ardenne) Troyes-Centre, Sainte-Savine Troyes-Sud, Saint-Julien-les-Villas, Tonnerre Lille, Reims Châtillon, Brienne, Bar sur Aube Chateauvillain, Châtillon, Bar sur Aube Border between Aube and Haute-Marne Chaumont, Semoutiers, St. Dizier Lyon-Dijon Metz-Nancy ==References== A05
